# Supabase advisor ratchet baseline — the KNOWN, pre-existing advisor backlog.
# One fingerprint per line: <category>:<cache_key>
#   - <category> is "security" or "performance" (the advisor's first category, lowercased).
#   - <cache_key> is Supabase's own stable advisor cache_key (verbatim, may contain
#     spaces/commas). Using it avoids reproduction drift when the /preflight gate
#     re-fingerprints live advisors.
# The `remote-supabase` preflight gate subtracts this set from live get_advisors output:
#   advisors NOT in this file are NEW (a real regression) and FAIL the gate; advisors
#   IN this file are the known backlog and render as a WARN-tier "N baselined" note.
# May shrink (as the backlog is burned down, re-run --update-advisors-baseline to
# tighten), should not grow without a deliberate decision. Refresh with:
#   /preflight --update-advisors-baseline
# Remediation of this backlog is tracked separately, see:
#   docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-01-supabase-advisor-backfill.md
